title: Fossambault-sur-le-Lac
text:
Fossambault-sur-le-Lac is a <a href="city%20%28Quebec%29">city</a> in the south part of <a href="Quebec">Quebec</a>, <a href="Canada">Canada</a>, in <a href="La%20Jacques-Cartier%20Regional%20County%20Municipality">La Jacques-Cartier Regional County Municipality</a>, just north of <a href="Quebec%20City">Quebec City</a>. It had a population of 1,613 as of the <a href="Canada%202011%20Census">Canada 2011 Census</a>. It is located near <a href="Saint-Joseph%20Lake">Saint-Joseph Lake</a>.
Demographics.
Population.
Private dwellings occupied by usual residents: 728 (total dwellings: 1,257)
Language.
Mother tongue:
Places of interest.
"<a href="Station%20Touristique%20Duchesnay">Station Touristique Duchesnay</a>" is one of the most attractive places of the town. The <a href="Jacques-Cartier%20River">Jacques-Cartier River</a> flows just nearby, and <a href="Route%20Fossambault">Route Fossambault</a> links the town to <a href="Sainte-Catherine-de-la-Jacques-Cartier">Sainte-Catherine-de-la-Jacques-Cartier</a>, where the <a href="Sainte%20Catherine%27s%20church">Sainte Catherine's church</a> is located. There is also a well-known hotel, called "Hotel de la Glace", with views overlooking the lake.
